Class Route

  • Object
    • Route
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Writeable

    public abstract class Route
extends Object
implements Writeable
    Represents a route in the transportation network.

    A route is essentially a collection of stops which public transport vehicles can follow.

    • Method Detail

      • decode

        public static Route decode(String routeString,
                           List<Stop> existingStops)
                    throws TransportFormatException
        Creates a new route object based on the given string representation.

        The format of the string should match that returned by the encode() method.

        The correct stop should also be added to the decoded route using the addStop(Stop) method.

        Parameters:
        routeString - The string to decode.
        existingStops - The stops which currently exist in the transport network.
        Returns:
        The decoded route object (a BusRoute, TrainRoute, or FerryRoute, depending on the type given in the string).
        Throws:
        TransportFormatException - If the given string or existingStops list is null, or the string is incorrectly formatted (according to the encode() representation). This includes, but is not limited to:
        1. A route type that is not one of "bus", "train", or "ferry".
        2. The route number is not an integer value.
        3. The stop name given in the string does not match one of the given existingStops.
        4. Any extra delimiters (, : |) being encountered whilst parsing.
        5. Any of the parts of the string being missing.
